 the modern age, and in doing so, argues that changes in making our meals—from shopping to cooking to dining—have created new cooks, new cooking categories, and new culinary challenges.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCookingzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamateur cooks.  aamerican cooking.  aamerican cuisine.  aanthropology of food.  achefs.  acooking at home.  acooking skills.  acreative process.  aculinary challenges.  adining.  afood and relationships.  ahome cooking.  ameal prep.  arelationships with food.  ashopping.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028922240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096397940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963979423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963979/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles